        <div class="trigger-desc">If request sits in "Under Review" past SLA target → auto-escalate to Approver's manager with full request context.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">IF status="Under Review" AND time_elapsed > SLA_target THEN escalate(approver.manager)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trigger-card">
        <div class="trigger-icon">⚠️</div>
        <div class="trigger-name">Capacity Conflict Detection</div>
        <div class="trigger-desc">If approved request would push any matched resource above 95% weighted utilization → flag for Approver review before deployment.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">IF resource.weighted_util + request.hours > 95% THEN flag("Capacity Conflict")</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trigger-card">
        <div class="trigger-icon">📦</div>
        <div class="trigger-name">Auto-Close</div>
        <div class="trigger-desc">Deployed requests auto-close 3 business days after the request end date if no further action is taken by the POC.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">IF status="Deployed" AND current_date > end_date + 3d THEN close(request)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trigger-card">
        <div class="trigger-icon">📊</div>
        <div class="trigger-name">Weekly Digest</div>
        <div class="trigger-desc">Summary email every Monday to all Approvers — open requests, avg response time, SLA compliance rate, and bottleneck processes.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">CRON: Monday 9:00 AM → email(all_approvers, weekly_summary)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trigger-card">
        <div class="trigger-icon">🔔</div>
        <div class="trigger-name">Deployment Confirmation Nudge</div>
        <div class="trigger-desc">If request reaches "Deployed" and POC hasn't confirmed within 24 hrs → auto-nudge POC to confirm resources are active.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">IF status="Deployed" AND !poc_confirmed AND time > 24h THEN nudge(requestor)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="trigger-card">
        <div class="trigger-icon">🔄</div>
        <div class="trigger-name">Demand Spike Auto-Alert</div>
        <div class="trigger-desc">If the Demand Forecast detects a process will exceed capacity within 2 weeks → auto-generate a pre-filled draft request for the relevant Approver.</div>
        <div class="trigger-rule">IF forecast.demand[+2wk] > capacity AND gap > 20hrs THEN draft_request(process, gap)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
